  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison writes: &quot;I am expecting that an article of mine will appear in the Independent to-morrow; and should my expectation be met, I desire Oliver to pay to you the $25 usually allowed in such cases, (very handsome pay, certainly,) instead of sending me a check for the same.&quot; Wendell Phillips Garrison is to use the money to buy two adding machines as Christmas presents for George Thompson Garrison and Francis Jackson Garrison. Also, he wants Wendell Phillips Garrison to buy &quot;a three dollar musical box&quot; for him. William L. Garrison reports that Richard Davis Webb &quot;gets about with less difficulty than when he first came to us.&quot; Deborah Webb has also improved in health. Francis Jackson Garrison has agreed to remain working for P. T. Jackson for $500 per year.</subfield>
